  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fcf7219bab7fe46a1ad266029b2fee19, type: 3}
  m_Name: Readme
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  icon: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 3a4a6becce6e9ba468b0e95045ea222e, type: 3}
  title: '2D AI Tool Pro: A complete framework and node editor.'
  sections:
  - heading: A big Thank you
    text: 'Firstly, I want to thank you for purchasing this tool and helping to make
      true the dreams of a fellow developer. You can open this ReadMe file again
      by selecting it in the Help folder or by Cliking -> Tools -> 2DAITool Help
      File '
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: Overview
    text: With this tool, you can create enemy behaviors, NPC movement, bosses in
      just a few steps to create your game faster and with fun, create quick prototypes,
      make super complex and fun enemies or create simple enemies/NPCs(You decide).
      This tool comes with 27 fully documented states ready to be used in your projects.
      In addition, you can create your states and behavior by following the API documentation
      and tutorial on the website or PDF documentation offline.
    linkText: Check the online documentation
    url: https://maykerstudio.gitlab.io/AI2DTool/
  - heading: Third party tools
    text: 'This package uses 3 third party projects to make things easy for everyone,
      which is: Editor Toolbox, xNode and NavMeshPlus2D. The only one that you need
      to know how it works is the NavMeshPlus2D, because it''s how we use Pathfinding
      in 2D using the built-in Unity Navmesh (Check documentation). But if you want
      to use the others tool to make things in your project you can check they GitHub
      pages on the links below (Send they some love too). Furthermore, we have integrations
      with A* Pathfinding project from Aron Granberg.'
    linkText: 
    url: 
  - heading: 
    text: 
    linkText: Editor Toolbox
    url: https://github.com/arimger/Unity-Editor-Toolbox
  - heading: 
    text: 
    linkText: xNode
    url: https://github.com/neoneper/xNode/
  - heading: Demo scenes
    text: This package comes with two demo scenes (For platformer and top-down) that
      will show an overview of what you can do with this tool. The sprites, animations,
      and tilesets were created by the talented Ansimuz, the license of the art is
      CC0 (Public-domain).
    linkText: Check ansimuz itch.io page
    url: https://ansimuz.itch.io
  - heading: Got feedback?
    text: Please reach us about the tool in the discord server
    linkText: Discord
    url: https://discord.gg/xMAFUksdz9
  - heading: Before playing the demo
    text: For the entities in the demo scenes to work correctly, you need to set
      up the layers on the section below, because we can't automatically create layers
      in your project (This could break your existing layers if we do that). So,
      I recommend that you put enemies and players in different layers, also, 'WhatIsGround'
      is the same thing as "WhatIsObstacles", this will be the layer where all your
      platforms, walls, obstacles will be. Also, the projectiles should be on their
      respective layer too. Also, you need to bake the NavMesh2D.
    linkText: 
    url: 
  hasShowedOnce: 1
